        "id": "q1",
        "questionSubtype": "mcq",
        "question": "Which of the following best defines a Rational Number?",
        "options": [
          "A. A number with a non-terminating, non-repeating decimal expansion",
          "B. A number that can be expressed in the form p/q where p and q are integers and q ≠ 0",
          "C. A number that cannot be written as a fraction",
          "D. A number that is always positive"
        ],
        "answer": "B. A number that can be expressed in the form p/q where p and q are integers and q ≠ 0",
        "explanation": "Rational numbers are defined by their ability to be written as a ratio of two integers (p/q) with a non-zero denominator.",
